# Manual HTTP probes for the catalog module (Phase 2 / Slice 3).
#
# How to use:
#   1. Start the server with `task run`.
#   2. Open this file in JetBrains GoLand/IntelliJ or in VSCode with the
#      REST Client extension installed.
#   3. Click the gutter icon next to a request to send it.
#
# Substitute <bookId> / <copyId> after the first POST returns.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### POST {{baseUrl}}/books — add a book
POST {{baseUrl}}/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Pragmatic Programmer",
  "authors": ["Andrew Hunt", "David Thomas"],
  "isbn": "978-0135957059"
}

### GET {{baseUrl}}/books — list every book
GET {{baseUrl}}/books

### GET {{baseUrl}}/books/{isbn} — find a book by ISBN
GET {{baseUrl}}/books/978-0135957059

### PATCH {{baseUrl}}/books/<bookId> — update title only
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/books/<bookId>
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "The Pragmatic Programmer, 20th Anniversary Edition"
}

### DELETE {{baseUrl}}/books/<bookId> — delete a book
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/books/<bookId>

### POST {{baseUrl}}/books/<bookId>/copies — register a physical copy
POST {{baseUrl}}/books/<bookId>/copies
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "condition": "GOOD"
}

### PATCH {{baseUrl}}/copies/<copyId>/available — mark a copy available
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/copies/<copyId>/available

### PATCH {{baseUrl}}/copies/<copyId>/unavailable — mark a copy unavailable
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/copies/<copyId>/unavailable
